! Full euv and X-ray images
! SDO(AIA) - 6 bands of EUV
! Hinode(XRT) - XRT (three channels)
! STEREO A (EUVI-A)
! STEREO B (EUVI-B)
!-------------------------
! Position files should be in HGI Coordinates, 
! !!!!NOTE!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
! Time as set in PARAM.in
! filw should coinside with the 
! observation time
!-------------------------
!To download the orbit for STEREO A use
!>wget ftp://mussel.srl.caltech.edu/pub/stereo/Position/ahead//position_ahead_2011_HCI.txt
!
!For STEREO B use
!wget ftp://mussel.srl.caltech.edu/pub/stereo/Position/behind/position_behind_2011_HCI.txt
!The positions of the satellite (three last numers in each line) should be normalized by R_sun.
!To achieve this the data should be divided by 696000 (km)
!
!To take the Earth coordinates in HGI, one should manually modify Param/HELIOSPHERE/Earth_Traj.in
!file: put there the desired date/time, change coordinate system to HGI and reduce time interval
!for output (0.0  0.0  10.0) Then three coordinates of the Earth position in HGI will be printed
!The output is for 2011/03/07 UT2-:00 

#LOOKUPTABLE
AiaXrt                  NameTable
load                    TypeAction
Param/los_tbl.dat       NameFile
ascii                   TypeFIle

#LOOKUPTABLE
EuviA                   NameTable
load                    TypeAction
Param/ResEuviA.dat      NameFile
ascii                   TypeFile

#LOOKUPTABLE
EuviB                   NameTable
load                    TypeAction
Param/ResEuviB.dat      NameFIle
ascii                   TypeFIle



